HEADWORD: Skewbald
<hw>Skew"bald`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Marked with spots
and patches of white and some color other than black; -- usually
distinguished from <xex>piebald</xex>, in which the colors are properly
white and black. Said of horses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skewer</ent>⟦br⟧
